17:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Process Street is best suited for operations teams, onboarding, compliance, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Slack Workflows, meanwhile, shines for Slack teams, internal processes, onboarding, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2014, Process Street describes itself as \"AI-powered workflow and checklist platform for recurring processes.\" Slack Workflows, established in 2013, positions itself as \"Built-in Slack automation for team communication and process workflows.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
18:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Process Street** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (7.0 vs 6.0). However, this does not mean Slack Workflows is a poor choice — far from it. Slack Workflows excels in its own right, particularly for Slack teams and internal processes.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent for documenting and running processes, go with Process Street. If built into slack—zero extra cost matters more to you, Slack Workflows is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
